  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1985-03-28", 
    "text": "Amends the Voting Rights Act of 1965 to prohibit any requirement that provides that a Federal primary candidate must receive a majority of the votes, rather than a plurality, to achieve the nomination. Deems such a requirement a procedure to deny or abridge the right to vote on account of race."
